CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1955, pg. 32, reads: "Association's Local President - Al D'Alessandro, president of the Western Pennsylvania Independent Automobile Dealers Association, one of the members of the National Independent Automobile Dealers Association, is set to welcome delegates to the Auto Dealers' ninth annual convention.  D'Alessandro exemplifies the many used car dealers.  He specializes in the sale of used Cadillacs and is pictured in his showroom at 2115 West Liberty Avenue. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Al D'Alessandro holding sign inscribed "Plan now to attend 9th Annual Convention National NIADA October 16, 17, 18, Wm. Penn Hotel Pittsburgh Pa" over hood of car, in his used car showroom, 2115 West Liberty Avenue
